110bool File__ReferenceFilesHelper_Algo1 (const sequence* Ref1, const sequence* Ref2) { return (Ref1->StreamID<Ref2->StreamID);}
111bool File__ReferenceFilesHelper_Algo2 (const sequence* Ref1, const sequence* Ref2) { return (Ref1->StreamPos<Ref2->StreamPos);}
112bool File__ReferenceFilesHelper_Algo3 (const sequence* Ref1, const sequence* Ref2) { return (Ref1->StreamKind<Ref2->StreamKind);}
113void File__ReferenceFilesHelper_InfoFromFileName (sequences &Sequences)
114{
115 ZtringListList List;
116 vector<size_t> Iterators;
117
118 for (size_t Sequences_Pos=0; Sequences_Pos<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Pos++)
119 {
120 ZtringList List2;
121 List2.Separator_Set(0, __T(" "));
122 if (Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->StreamKind==Stream_Audio && !Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->FileNames.empty())
123 {
124 Ztring Name=Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->FileNames[0];
125 while (Name.FindAndReplace(__T("51 "), Ztring()));
126 while (Name.FindAndReplace(__T("_"), __T(" ")));
127 while (Name.FindAndReplace(__T("."), __T(" ")));
128 while (Name.FindAndReplace(__T(" "), __T(" ")));
129 size_t PathSeparator_Pos=Name.rfind(PathSeparator);
130 if (PathSeparator_Pos!=(size_t)-1)
131 Name.erase(0, PathSeparator_Pos+1);
132
133 //Removing extension
134 if (Name.size()>4 && Name.rfind(__T('.'))==Name.size())
135 Name.resize(Name.size()-4);
136
137 List2.Write(Name);
138 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<List2.size(); Pos++)
139 List2[Pos].MakeLowerCase();
140 List.push_back(List2);
141 Iterators.push_back(Sequences_Pos);
142 }
143 }
144
145 if (List.size()<2)
146 return;
147
148 size_t ChannelLayout_Pos=(size_t)-1;
149 size_t Language_Pos=(size_t)-1;
150 for (size_t Pos2=0; Pos2<List[0].size(); Pos2++)
151 {
152 bool IsChannelLayout=true;
153 bool IsLanguage=true;
154 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<List.size(); Pos++)
155 {
156 if (Pos2>=List[Pos].size())
157 break; //Maybe begin of title
158 const Ztring &Test=List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-Pos2];
159
160 //ChannelLayout
161 if (ChannelLayout_Pos==(size_t)-1
162 && Test!=__T("l")
163 && Test!=__T("r")
164 && Test!=__T("lt")
165 && Test!=__T("rt")
166 && Test!=__T("c")
167 && Test!=__T("lf")
168 && Test!=__T("lfe")
169 && Test!=__T("sub")
170 && Test!=__T("ls")
171 && Test!=__T("rs")
172 && Test!=__T("b")
173 && Test!=__T("mono"))
174 IsChannelLayout=false;
175
176 //Language
177 if (Language_Pos==(size_t)-1
178 && Test!=__T("ara")
179 && Test!=__T("deu")
180 && Test!=__T("eng")
181 && Test!=__T("fra")
182 && Test!=__T("fre")
183 && Test!=__T("ita")
184 && Test!=__T("jpn")
185 && Test!=__T("rus")
186 && Test!=__T("spa"))
187 IsLanguage=false;
188 }
189
190 if (IsChannelLayout && ChannelLayout_Pos==(size_t)-1)
191 ChannelLayout_Pos=Pos2;
192 if (IsLanguage && Language_Pos==(size_t)-1)
193 Language_Pos=Pos2;
194 if (ChannelLayout_Pos!=(size_t)-1 && Language_Pos!=(size_t)-1)
195 break;
196 }
197
198 //ChannelLayout
199 if (ChannelLayout_Pos!=(size_t)-1)
200 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<List.size(); Pos++)
201 {
202 Ztring ChannelPositions, ChannelPositions2, ChannelLayout;
203 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("l"))
204 {
205 ChannelPositions=__T("Front: L");
206 ChannelPositions2=__T("1/0/0");
207 ChannelLayout=__T("L");
208 }
209 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("lt"))
210 {
211 ChannelPositions=__T("Front: Lt");
212 ChannelPositions2=__T("1/0/0");
213 ChannelLayout=__T("Lt");
214 }
215 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("rt"))
216 {
217 ChannelPositions=__T("Front: Rt");
218 ChannelPositions2=__T("1/0/0");
219 ChannelLayout=__T("Rt");
220 }
221 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("r"))
222 {
223 ChannelPositions=__T("Front: R");
224 ChannelPositions2=__T("1/0/0");
225 ChannelLayout=__T("R");
226 }
227 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("c") || List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("mono"))
228 {
229 ChannelPositions=__T("Front: C");
230 ChannelPositions2=__T("1/0/0");
231 ChannelLayout=__T("C");
232 }
233 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("lf") || List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("lfe") || List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("sub"))
234 {
235 ChannelPositions=__T("LFE");
236 ChannelPositions2=__T(".1");
237 ChannelLayout=__T("LFE");
238 }
239 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("ls"))
240 {
241 ChannelPositions=__T("Side: L");
242 ChannelPositions2=__T("0/1/0");
243 ChannelLayout=__T("Ls");
244 }
245 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("rs"))
246 {
247 ChannelPositions=__T("Side: R");
248 ChannelPositions2=__T("0/1/0");
249 ChannelLayout=__T("Rs");
250 }
251 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-ChannelLayout_Pos]==__T("b"))
252 {
253 ChannelPositions=__T("Back: C");
254 ChannelPositions2=__T("0/0/1");
255 ChannelLayout=__T("Cs");
256 }
257
258 Sequences[Iterators[Pos]]->Infos["ChannelPositions"]=ChannelPositions;
259 Sequences[Iterators[Pos]]->Infos["ChannelPositions/String2"]=ChannelPositions2;
260 Sequences[Iterators[Pos]]->Infos["ChannelLayout"]=ChannelLayout;
261 }
262
263 //Language
264 if (Language_Pos!=(size_t)-1)
265 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<List.size(); Pos++)
266 if (1+Language_Pos<List[Pos].size())
267 {
268 Ztring Language;
269 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-Language_Pos]==__T("ara"))
270 Language=__T("ar");
271 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-Language_Pos]==__T("deu"))
272 Language=__T("de");
273 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-Language_Pos]==__T("eng"))
274 Language=__T("en");
275 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-Language_Pos]==__T("fra") || List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-Language_Pos]==__T("fre"))
276 Language=__T("fr");
277 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-Language_Pos]==__T("ita"))
278 Language=__T("it");
279 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-Language_Pos]==__T("jpn"))
280 Language=__T("ja");
281 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-Language_Pos]==__T("rus"))
282 Language=__T("ru");
283 if (List[Pos][List[Pos].size()-1-Language_Pos]==__T("spa"))
284 Language=__T("es");
285
286 if (!Language.empty())
287 Sequences[Iterators[Pos]]->Infos["Language"]=Language;
288 }
289}

295//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
296void File__ReferenceFilesHelper::AddSequence(sequence* NewSequence)
297{
298 Common->HasMultipleSequences=!Sequences.empty(); //If not empty, there will be more than 1 sequence just after
299
300 NewSequence->Package=Common;
301 NewSequence->Common->Package=Common;
302
303 Sequences.push_back(NewSequence);
304}

306//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
307void File__ReferenceFilesHelper::UpdateFileName(const Ztring& OldFileName, const Ztring& NewFileName)
308{
309 size_t Sequences_Size=Sequences.size();
310 for (size_t Sequences_Pos=0; Sequences_Pos<Sequences_Size; ++Sequences_Pos)
311 {
312 sequence* Sequence=Sequences[Sequences_Pos];
313
314 Sequence->UpdateFileName(OldFileName, NewFileName);
315 }
316}

318//***************************************************************************
319// Streams management
320//***************************************************************************
321
322void File__ReferenceFilesHelper::ParseReferences()
323{
324 if (!Init_Done)
325 {
326 #if MEDIAINFO_FILTER
327 if (MI->Config->File_Filter_Audio_Get())
328 {
329 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Sequences.size(); Pos++)
330 if (Sequences[Pos]->StreamKind!=Stream_Audio)
331 {
332 Sequences.erase(Sequences.begin()+Pos);
333 Pos--;
334 }
335 CountOfReferencesToParse=Sequences.size();
336 }
337 #endif //MEDIAINFO_FILTER
338
339 //Filling Filenames from the more complete version and Edit rates
340 float64 EditRate=DBL_MAX;
341 size_t EditRate_Count=0;
342 for (Sequences_Current=0; Sequences_Current<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Current++)
343 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames.empty())
344 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size(); Pos++)
345 {
346 for (size_t Resource_FileNames_Pos=0; Resource_FileNames_Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames.size(); Resource_FileNames_Pos++)
347 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames.push_back(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames[Resource_FileNames_Pos]);
348 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->EditRate && EditRate!=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->EditRate)
349 {
350 if (EditRate>Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->EditRate)
351 EditRate=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->EditRate;
352 EditRate_Count++;
353 }
354 }
355 if (EditRate_Count>1)
356 //Multiple rates, using only one rate
357 for (Sequences_Current=0; Sequences_Current<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Current++)
358 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size(); Pos++)
359 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->EditRate && EditRate!=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->EditRate)
360 {
361 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsBefore)
362 {
363 float64 Temp=(float64)Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsBefore;
364 Temp/=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->EditRate;
365 Temp*=EditRate;
366 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsBefore=float64_int64s(Temp);
367 }
368 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfter!=(int64u)-1)
369 {
370 float64 Temp=(float64)Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfter;
371 Temp/=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->EditRate;
372 Temp*=EditRate;
373 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfter=float64_int64s(Temp);
374 }
375 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfterDuration!=(int64u)-1)
376 {
377 float64 Temp=(float64)Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfterDuration;
378 Temp/=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->EditRate;
379 Temp*=EditRate;
380 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfterDuration=float64_int64s(Temp);
381 }
382 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->EditRate=EditRate;
383 }
384
385 //Testing IDs
386 std::set<int64u> StreamList;
387 bool StreamList_DuplicatedIds=false;
388 for (Sequences_Current=0; Sequences_Current<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Current++)
389 if (StreamList.find(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamID)==StreamList.end())
390 StreamList.insert(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamID);
391 else
392 {
393 StreamList_DuplicatedIds=true;
394 break;
395 }
396 if (StreamList_DuplicatedIds)
397 for (Sequences_Current=0; Sequences_Current<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Current++)
398 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamID=Sequences_Current+1;
399 if (Sequences.size()==1 && (*Sequences.begin())->StreamID==(int64u)-1)
400 {
401 ContainerHasNoId=true;
402 #if MEDIAINFO_EVENTS
403 MI->StreamIDs_Width[MI->StreamIDs_Size-1]=0;
404 #endif //MEDIAINFO_EVENTS
405 }
406 std::sort(Sequences.begin(), Sequences.end(), File__ReferenceFilesHelper_Algo1);
407 std::sort(Sequences.begin(), Sequences.end(), File__ReferenceFilesHelper_Algo2);
408 std::sort(Sequences.begin(), Sequences.end(), File__ReferenceFilesHelper_Algo3);
409
410 //InfoFromFileName
411 File__ReferenceFilesHelper_InfoFromFileName(Sequences);
412
413 #if MEDIAINFO_EVENTS
414 if (MI->Config->Config_PerPackage==NULL)
415 {
416 MI->Config->Config_PerPackage=new MediaInfo_Config_PerPackage;
417 MI->Config->Config_PerPackage->CountOfPackages=Sequences.size();
418 }
419 #endif //MEDIAINFO_EVENTS
420
421 //Configuring file names
422 Sequences_Current=0;
423 while (Sequences_Current<Sequences.size())
424 {
425 ZtringList Names=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames;
426 ZtringList AbsoluteNames; AbsoluteNames.Separator_Set(0, ",");
427 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Names.size(); Pos++)
428 {
429 if (Names[Pos].find(__T("file:///"))==0)
430 {
431 Names[Pos].erase(0, 8); //Removing "file:///", this is the default behaviour and this makes comparison easier
432 Names[Pos]=ZenLib::Format::Http::URL_Encoded_Decode(Names[Pos]);
433 }
434 if (Names[Pos].find(__T("file://"))==0)
435 {
436 Names[Pos].erase(0, 7); //Removing "file://", this is the default behaviour and this makes comparison easier
437 Names[Pos]=ZenLib::Format::Http::URL_Encoded_Decode(Names[Pos]);
438 }
439 if (Names[Pos].find(__T("file:"))==0)
440 {
441 Names[Pos].erase(0, 5); //Removing "file:", this is the default behaviour and this makes comparison easier
442 Names[Pos]=ZenLib::Format::Http::URL_Encoded_Decode(Names[Pos]);
443 }
444 Ztring AbsoluteName;
445 if (Names[Pos].find(__T(':'))!=1 && Names[Pos].find(__T("/"))!=0 && Names[Pos].find(__T("\\\\"))!=0) //If absolute patch
446 {
447 if (MI->File_Name.find(__T("://"))==string::npos)
448 AbsoluteName=ZenLib::FileName::Path_Get(MI->File_Name);
449 else
450 {
451 size_t Pos_Path=MI->File_Name.find_last_of('/');
452 if (Pos_Path!=Ztring::npos)
453 AbsoluteName=MI->File_Name.substr(0, Pos_Path);
454 }
455 if (!AbsoluteName.empty())
456 AbsoluteName+=ZenLib::PathSeparator;
457 }
458 AbsoluteName+=Names[Pos];
459 #ifdef __WINDOWS__
460 if (AbsoluteName.find(__T("://"))==string::npos)
461 AbsoluteName.FindAndReplace(__T("/"), __T("\\"), 0, Ztring_Recursive); //Names[Pos] normalization local file
462 else
463 AbsoluteName.FindAndReplace(__T("\\"), __T("/"), 0, Ztring_Recursive); //Names[Pos] normalization with protocol (so "/" in all cases)
464 #endif //__WINDOWS__
465 AbsoluteNames.push_back(AbsoluteName);
466 }
467 if (AbsoluteNames.empty() || !(AbsoluteNames[0].find(__T("://"))!=string::npos || File::Exists(AbsoluteNames[0])))
468 {
469 AbsoluteNames.clear();
470
471 //Configuring file name (this time, we try to force URL decode in all cases)
472 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Names.size(); Pos++)
473 {
474 Names[Pos]=ZenLib::Format::Http::URL_Encoded_Decode(Names[Pos]);
475 Ztring AbsoluteName;
476 if (Names[Pos].find(__T(':'))!=1 && Names[Pos].find(__T("/"))!=0 && Names[Pos].find(__T("\\\\"))!=0) //If absolute patch
477 {
478 if (MI->File_Name.find(__T("://"))==string::npos)
479 AbsoluteName=ZenLib::FileName::Path_Get(MI->File_Name);
480 else
481 {
482 size_t Pos_Path=MI->File_Name.find_last_of('/');
483 if (Pos_Path!=Ztring::npos)
484 AbsoluteName=MI->File_Name.substr(0, Pos_Path);
485 }
486 if (!AbsoluteName.empty())
487 AbsoluteName+=ZenLib::PathSeparator;
488 }
489 AbsoluteName+=Names[Pos];
490 #ifdef __WINDOWS__
491 AbsoluteName.FindAndReplace(__T("/"), __T("\\"), 0, Ztring_Recursive); //Names[Pos] normalization
492 #endif //__WINDOWS__
493 AbsoluteNames.push_back(AbsoluteName);
494 }
495
496 if (AbsoluteNames.empty() || !File::Exists(AbsoluteNames[0]))
497 {
498 AbsoluteNames.clear();
499 Names=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames;
500
501 //Configuring file name (this time, we try to test local files)
502 size_t PathSeparator_Pos=Names.empty()?string::npos:Names[0].find_last_of(__T("\\/"));
503 if (PathSeparator_Pos!=string::npos && PathSeparator_Pos)
504 {
505 Ztring PathToRemove=Names[0].substr(0, PathSeparator_Pos);
506 bool IsOk=true;
507 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Names.size(); Pos++)
508 if (Names[Pos].find(PathToRemove))
509 {
510 IsOk=false;
511 break;
512 }
513 if (IsOk)
514 {
515 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Names.size(); Pos++)
516 {
517 Names[Pos].erase(0, PathSeparator_Pos+1);
518 Ztring AbsoluteName;
519 if (MI->File_Name.find(__T("://"))==string::npos)
520 AbsoluteName=ZenLib::FileName::Path_Get(MI->File_Name);
521 else
522 {
523 size_t Pos_Path=MI->File_Name.find_last_of('/');
524 if (Pos_Path!=Ztring::npos)
525 AbsoluteName=MI->File_Name.substr(0, Pos_Path);
526 }
527 if (!AbsoluteName.empty())
528 AbsoluteName+=ZenLib::PathSeparator;
529 AbsoluteName+=Names[Pos];
530 #ifdef __WINDOWS__
531 if (AbsoluteName.find(__T("://"))==string::npos)
532 AbsoluteName.FindAndReplace(__T("/"), __T("\\"), 0, Ztring_Recursive); //Names[Pos] normalization local file
533 else
534 AbsoluteName.FindAndReplace(__T("\\"), __T("/"), 0, Ztring_Recursive); //Names[Pos] normalization with protocol (so "/" in all cases)
535 #endif //__WINDOWS__
536 AbsoluteNames.push_back(AbsoluteName);
537 }
538
539 if (!File::Exists(AbsoluteNames[0]))
540 {
541 AbsoluteNames.clear();
542 Names=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames;
543
544 //Configuring file name (this time, we try to test local files)
545 size_t PathSeparator_Pos=Names[0].find_last_of(__T("\\/"));
546 if (PathSeparator_Pos!=string::npos && PathSeparator_Pos)
547 PathSeparator_Pos=Names[0].find_last_of(__T("\\/"), PathSeparator_Pos-1);
548 if (PathSeparator_Pos!=string::npos && PathSeparator_Pos)
549 {
550 Ztring PathToRemove=Names[0].substr(0, PathSeparator_Pos);
551 bool IsOk=true;
552 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Names.size(); Pos++)
553 if (Names[Pos].find(PathToRemove))
554 {
555 IsOk=false;
556 break;
557 }
558 if (IsOk)
559 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Names.size(); Pos++)
560 {
561 Names[Pos].erase(0, PathSeparator_Pos+1);
562 Ztring AbsoluteName;
563 if (MI->File_Name.find(__T("://"))==string::npos)
564 AbsoluteName=ZenLib::FileName::Path_Get(MI->File_Name);
565 else
566 {
567 size_t Pos_Path=MI->File_Name.find_last_of('/');
568 if (Pos_Path!=Ztring::npos)
569 AbsoluteName=MI->File_Name.substr(0, Pos_Path);
570 }
571 if (!AbsoluteName.empty())
572 AbsoluteName+=ZenLib::PathSeparator;
573 AbsoluteName+=Names[Pos];
574 #ifdef __WINDOWS__
575 AbsoluteName.FindAndReplace(__T("/"), __T("\\"), 0, Ztring_Recursive); //Names[Pos] normalization
576 #endif //__WINDOWS__
577 AbsoluteNames.push_back(AbsoluteName);
578 }
579 }
580
581 if (!AbsoluteNames.empty() && !File::Exists(AbsoluteNames[0]))
582 AbsoluteNames.clear();
583 }
584 }
585 }
586 }
587 }
588 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Source=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames.Read(0);
589 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind!=Stream_Max && !Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Source.empty())
590 {
591 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos==(size_t)-1)
592 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos=Stream_Prepare(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind);
593 MI->Fill(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos, "Source", Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Source);
594 }
595 if (!AbsoluteNames.empty())
596 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames=AbsoluteNames;
597
598 if (!AbsoluteNames.empty() && AbsoluteNames[0]==MI->File_Name)
599 {
600 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->IsCircular=true;
601 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames.clear();
602 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status.set(File__Analyze::IsFinished);
603 }
604 else if (!AbsoluteNames.empty())
605 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames=AbsoluteNames;
606 else
607 {
608 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status.set(File__Analyze::IsFinished);
609 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind!=Stream_Max && !Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Source.empty())
610 {
611 MI->Fill(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos, "Source_Info", "Missing");
612 if (MI->Retrieve(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos, General_ID).empty() && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamID!=(int64u)-1)
613 MI->Fill(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos, General_ID, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamID);
614 for (std::map<string, Ztring>::iterator Info=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Infos.begin(); Info!=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Infos.end(); ++Info)
615 {
616 if (Info->first=="CodecID")
617 MI->CodecID_Fill(Info->second, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos, InfoCodecID_Format_Mpeg4);
618 else
619 MI->Fill(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos, Info->first.c_str(), Info->second);
620 }
621 }
622 }
623
624 if (FilesForStorage)
625 {
626 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames.size(); Pos++)
627 {
628 if (Pos==Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size())
629 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.push_back(new resource);
630 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames.clear();
631 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames.push_back(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames[Pos]);
632 }
633 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames.resize(1);
634 }
635
636 Sequences_Current++;
637 }
638
639 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
640 if (Config->NextPacket_Get())
641 {
642 Demux_Interleave=Config->File_Demux_Interleave_Get();
643 if (Demux_Interleave)
644 {
645 CountOfReferencesToParse=Sequences.size();
646 for (sequences::iterator ReferenceSource=Sequences.begin(); ReferenceSource!=Sequences.end(); ++ReferenceSource)
647 if ((*ReferenceSource)->FileNames.empty())
648 CountOfReferencesToParse--;
649 DTS_Interval=250000000LL; // 250 milliseconds
650 }
651 }
652 else
653 Demux_Interleave=false;
654
655 //Using the frame rate from the first stream having a frame rate
656 if (!FrameRate)
657 for (sequences::iterator ReferenceFrameRate=Sequences.begin(); ReferenceFrameRate!=Sequences.end(); ++ReferenceFrameRate)
658 if ((*ReferenceFrameRate)->FrameRate)
659 {
660 FrameRate=(*ReferenceFrameRate)->FrameRate;
661 break;
662 }
663
664 if (Config->NextPacket_Get())
665 {
666 Sequences_Current=0;
667 while (Sequences_Current<Sequences.size())
668 {
669 ParseReference(); //Init
670 Sequences_Current++;
671 }
672
673 //Cleanup
674 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Sequences.size(); Pos++)
675 if (Sequences[Pos]->Status[File__Analyze::IsFinished])
676 {
677 Sequences.erase(Sequences.begin()+Pos);
678 Pos--;
679 }
680 CountOfReferencesToParse=Sequences.size();
681 if (Sequences.empty())
682 return;
683
684 //File size handling
685 if (MI->Config->File_Size!=MI->File_Size)
686 {
687 MI->Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_FileSize, MI->Config->File_Size, 10, true);
688 MI->Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_StreamSize, MI->File_Size, 10, true);
689 }
690
691 }
692 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
693
694 FileSize_Compute();
695 Sequences_Current=0;
696 CountOfReferences_ForReadSize=Sequences.size();
697 Init_Done=true;
698
699 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
700 if (Config->NextPacket_Get() && MI->Demux_EventWasSent_Accept_Specific)
701 {
702 MI->Config->Demux_EventWasSent=true;
703 return;
704 }
705 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
706 }
707
708 while (Sequences_Current<Sequences.size())
709 {
710 #if MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
711 if (!Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status[File__Analyze::IsFinished])
712 #endif //MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
713 ParseReference();
714
715 //State
716 int64u FileSize_Parsed=0;
717 #if MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
718 DTS_Minimal=(int64u)-1;
719 #endif //MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
720 for (sequences::iterator ReferenceTemp=Sequences.begin(); ReferenceTemp!=Sequences.end(); ++ReferenceTemp)
721 {
722 if ((*ReferenceTemp)->MI)
723 {
724 if ((*ReferenceTemp)->State<10000)
725 {
726 if ((*ReferenceTemp)->MI)
727 (*ReferenceTemp)->State=(*ReferenceTemp)->MI->State_Get();
728 if ((*ReferenceTemp)->State && (*ReferenceTemp)->MI->Config.File_Size!=(int64u)-1)
729 FileSize_Parsed+=(int64u)((*ReferenceTemp)->MI->Config.File_Size*(((float)(*ReferenceTemp)->State)/10000));
730 }
731 else
732 FileSize_Parsed+=(*ReferenceTemp)->MI->Config.File_Size;
733
734 #if MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
735 //Minimal DTS
736 if (DTS_Interval!=(int64u)-1 && !Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status[File__Analyze::IsFinished] && ((*ReferenceTemp)->Resources.empty() || (*ReferenceTemp)->Resources_Current<(*ReferenceTemp)->Resources.size()))
737 {
738 int64u DTS_Temp;
739 if (!(*ReferenceTemp)->Resources.empty() && (*ReferenceTemp)->Resources_Current)
740 {
741 if ((*ReferenceTemp)->Resources[(*ReferenceTemp)->Resources_Current]->MI->Info->FrameInfo.DTS!=(int64u)-1)
742 DTS_Temp=(*ReferenceTemp)->Resources[(*ReferenceTemp)->Resources_Current]->MI->Info->FrameInfo.DTS-(*ReferenceTemp)->Resources[(*ReferenceTemp)->Resources_Current]->MI->Info->Config->Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream;
743 else
744 DTS_Temp=0;
745 }
746 else
747 {
748 if ((*ReferenceTemp)->MI->Info->FrameInfo.DTS!=(int64u)-1)
749 DTS_Temp=(*ReferenceTemp)->MI->Info->FrameInfo.DTS-(*ReferenceTemp)->MI->Info->Config->Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream;
750 else
751 DTS_Temp=0;
752 }
753 DTS_Temp+=(*ReferenceTemp)->Resources[(*ReferenceTemp)->Resources_Current]->Demux_Offset_DTS;
754 if (DTS_Minimal>DTS_Temp)
755 DTS_Minimal=DTS_Temp;
756 }
757 #endif //MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
758 }
759 else
760 FileSize_Parsed+=(*ReferenceTemp)->FileSize;
761 }
762 Config->State_Set(((float)FileSize_Parsed)/MI->Config->File_Size);
763
764 #if MEDIAINFO_EVENTS
765 struct MediaInfo_Event_General_SubFile_End_0 Event;
766 MI->Event_Prepare((struct MediaInfo_Event_Generic*)&Event);
767 Event.EventCode=MediaInfo_EventCode_Create(0, MediaInfo_Event_General_SubFile_End, 0);
768 Event.EventSize=sizeof(struct MediaInfo_Event_General_SubFile_End_0);
769
770 MI->Config->Event_Send(NULL, (const int8u*)&Event, Event.EventSize, MI->File_Name);
771 #endif //MEDIAINFO_EVENTS
772
773 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
774 if (Demux_Interleave && (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI==NULL || Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Info==NULL || Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Info->Demux_CurrentParser==NULL || Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Info->Demux_CurrentParser->Demux_TotalBytes>=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Info->Demux_CurrentParser->Buffer_TotalBytes+Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Info->Demux_CurrentParser->Buffer_Size))
775 {
776 size_t Reference_Next=Sequences_Current; ++Reference_Next;
777
778 if (Reference_Next==Sequences.size() && Config->NextPacket_Get() && CountOfReferencesToParse)
779 Sequences_Current=0;
780 else
781 Sequences_Current=Reference_Next;
782
783 if (Config->Demux_EventWasSent)
784 return;
785 }
786 else
787 {
788 if (Config->Demux_EventWasSent)
789 return;
790
791 Sequences_Current++;
792 }
793 #else //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
794 Sequences_Current++;
795 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
796 }
797
798 //File size handling
799 FileSize_Compute();
800 if (MI->Config->File_Size!=MI->File_Size
801 #if MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
802 && !Config->File_IgnoreSequenceFileSize_Get()
803 #endif //MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
804 )
805 {
806 MI->Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_FileSize, MI->Config->File_Size, 10, true);
807 MI->Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_StreamSize, MI->File_Size, 10, true);
808 }
809 #if MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
810 if (Config->File_IgnoreSequenceFileSize_Get())
811 MI->Clear(Stream_General, 0, General_FileSize);
812 #endif //MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
813}

815//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
816bool File__ReferenceFilesHelper::ParseReference_Init()
817{
818 //Configuration
819 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI=MI_Create();
820 if (Config->ParseSpeed>=1)
821 {
822 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size(); Pos++)
823 {
824 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->EditRate)
825 {
826 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
827 if (Pos==0)
828 {
829 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->Demux_Offset_DTS=0;
830 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->Demux_Offset_Frame=0;
831 }
832 if (Pos+1<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size())
833 {
834 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos+1]->Demux_Offset_DTS=float64_int64s(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->Demux_Offset_DTS+(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfter-Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsBefore)/Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->EditRate*1000000000);
835 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos+1]->Demux_Offset_Frame=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->Demux_Offset_Frame+Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfter-Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsBefore;
836 }
837 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
838 }
839 else
840 {
841 MediaInfo_Internal MI2;
842 MI2.Option(__T("File_KeepInfo"), __T("1"));
843 Ztring ParseSpeed_Save=MI2.Option(__T("ParseSpeed_Get"), __T("0"));
844 Ztring Demux_Save=MI2.Option(__T("Demux_Get"), __T(""));
845 MI2.Option(__T("ParseSpeed"), __T("0"));
846 MI2.Option(__T("Demux"), Ztring());
847 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames.Separator_Set(0, ",");
848 size_t MiOpenResult=MI2.Open(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames.Read());
849 MI2.Option(__T("ParseSpeed"), ParseSpeed_Save); //This is a global value, need to reset it. TODO: local value
850 MI2.Option(__T("Demux"), Demux_Save); //This is a global value, need to reset it. TODO: local value
851 if (MiOpenResult)
852 {
853 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
854 int64u Duration=MI2.Get(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, 0, __T("Duration")).To_int64u()*1000000;
855 int64u FrameCount=MI2.Get(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, 0, __T("FrameCount")).To_int64u();
856 if (Pos==0)
857 {
858 int64u Delay=MI2.Get(Stream_Video, 0, Video_Delay).To_int64u()*1000000;
859 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind==Stream_Video && Offset_Video_DTS==0)
860 Offset_Video_DTS=Delay;
861 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->Demux_Offset_DTS=Offset_Video_DTS;
862 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->Demux_Offset_Frame=0;
863 }
864 if (Pos+1<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size())
865 {
866 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos+1]->Demux_Offset_DTS=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->Demux_Offset_DTS+Duration;
867 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos+1]->Demux_Offset_Frame=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->Demux_Offset_Frame+FrameCount;
868 }
869 else
870 Duration=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->Demux_Offset_DTS+Duration-Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->Demux_Offset_DTS;
871 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
872 }
873 }
874
875 if (Pos)
876 {
877 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->MI=MI_Create();
878 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->MI->Config.File_IgnoreEditsBefore=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsBefore;
879 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfter==(int64u)-1 && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfterDuration!=(int64u)-1)
880 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->MI->Config.File_IgnoreEditsAfter=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsBefore+Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfterDuration;
881 else
882 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->MI->Config.File_IgnoreEditsAfter=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->IgnoreEditsAfter;
883 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->MI->Config.File_EditRate=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->EditRate;
884 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
885 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_Frame=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->Demux_Offset_Frame;
886 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->Demux_Offset_DTS;
887 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
888 }
889 }
890 if (!Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.empty())
891 {
892 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.File_IgnoreEditsBefore=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->IgnoreEditsBefore;
893 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->IgnoreEditsAfter==(int64u)-1 && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->IgnoreEditsAfterDuration!=(int64u)-1)
894 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.File_IgnoreEditsAfter=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->IgnoreEditsBefore+Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->IgnoreEditsAfterDuration;
895 else
896 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.File_IgnoreEditsAfter=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->IgnoreEditsAfter;
897 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.File_EditRate=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->EditRate;
898 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
899 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_Frame=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->Demux_Offset_Frame;
900 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->Demux_Offset_DTS;
901 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
902 }
903 }
904
905 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->IsCircular)
906 {
907 MI->Fill(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos, "Source_Info", "Circular");
908 if (!Config->File_KeepInfo_Get())
909 {
910 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
911 if (CountOfReferencesToParse)
912 CountOfReferencesToParse--;
913 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
914 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind=Stream_Max;
915 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos=(size_t)-1;
916 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileSize=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.File_Size;
917 delete Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI; Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI=NULL;
918 }
919 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames.clear();
920 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status.set(File__Analyze::IsFinished);
921 }
922 else
923 {
924 //Run
925 #if MEDIAINFO_EVENTS
926 SubFile_Start();
927 #endif //MEDIAINFO_EVENTS
928 if (!Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Open(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames.Read()))
929 {
930 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind!=Stream_Max)
931 MI->Fill(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos, "Source_Info", "Missing", Unlimited, true, true);
932 if (!Config->File_KeepInfo_Get())
933 {
934 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
935 if (CountOfReferencesToParse)
936 CountOfReferencesToParse--;
937 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
938 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind=Stream_Max;
939 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos=(size_t)-1;
940 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileSize=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.File_Size;
941 delete Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI; Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI=NULL;
942 }
943 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status.set(File__Analyze::IsFinished);
944 }
945
946 if (Config->ParseSpeed>=1)
947 for (size_t Pos=1; Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size(); Pos++)
948 {
949 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames.Separator_Set(0, ",");
950 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->MI->Open(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames.Read());
951 }
952
953 #if MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET && MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
954 if (Config->NextPacket_Get())
955 return false;
956 #endif //MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
957 }
958
959 return true;
960}
961
962//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
963void File__ReferenceFilesHelper::ParseReference()
964{
965 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI==NULL && !Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames.empty())
966 {
967 if (!ParseReference_Init())
968 return;
969 }
970
971 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI)
972 {
973 #if MEDIAINFO_EVENTS && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
974 if (DTS_Interval!=(int64u)-1 && !Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status[File__Analyze::IsFinished] && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Info->FrameInfo.DTS!=(int64u)-1 && DTS_Minimal!=(int64u)-1 && (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.empty() || Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size()))
975 {
976 int64u DTS_Temp;
977 if (!Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.empty() && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current)
978 {
979 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->MI->Info->FrameInfo.DTS!=(int64u)-1)
980 DTS_Temp=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->MI->Info->FrameInfo.DTS-Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->MI->Info->Config->Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream;
981 else
982 DTS_Temp=0;
983 }
984 else
985 {
986 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Info->FrameInfo.DTS!=(int64u)-1)
987 DTS_Temp=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Info->FrameInfo.DTS-Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Info->Config->Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream;
988 else
989 DTS_Temp=0;
990 }
991 DTS_Temp+=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->Demux_Offset_DTS;
992 if (!Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.empty() && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size() && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->EditRate && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->IgnoreEditsBefore)
993 {
994 int64u TimeOffset=float64_int64s(((float64)Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->IgnoreEditsBefore)/Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->EditRate*1000000000);
995 if (DTS_Temp>TimeOffset)
996 DTS_Temp-=TimeOffset;
997 else
998 DTS_Temp=0;
999 }
1000 if (DTS_Temp>DTS_Minimal+DTS_Interval)
1001 return;
1002 }
1003 if (Config->Event_CallBackFunction_IsSet() && !Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status[File__Analyze::IsFinished])
1004 {
1005 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1006 SubFile_Start();
1007 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current==0)
1008 {
1009 while ((Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Open_NextPacket())[8])
1010 {
1011 if (!Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileSize_IsPresent && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.File_Size!=(int64u)-1)
1012 {
1013 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileSize_IsPresent=true;
1014 if (CountOfReferences_ForReadSize)
1015 {
1016 CountOfReferences_ForReadSize--;
1017 if (!CountOfReferences_ForReadSize)
1018 CountOfReferences_ForReadSize_Run();
1019 }
1020 }
1021
1022 if (Config->Event_CallBackFunction_IsSet())
1023 {
1024 Config->Demux_EventWasSent=true;
1025 return;
1026 }
1027 }
1028 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current++;
1029 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size() && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->MI)
1030 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->MI->Open_Buffer_Seek(0, 0, (int64u)-1);
1031 }
1032
1033 #if MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET && MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1034 if (Config->ParseSpeed<1.0)
1035 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size(); //No need to parse all files
1036 #endif //MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1037
1038 while (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size())
1039 {
1040 while ((Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->MI->Open_NextPacket())[8])
1041 {
1042 if (!Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileSize_IsPresent && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.File_Size!=(int64u)-1)
1043 {
1044 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileSize_IsPresent=true;
1045 if (CountOfReferences_ForReadSize)
1046 {
1047 CountOfReferences_ForReadSize--;
1048 if (!CountOfReferences_ForReadSize)
1049 CountOfReferences_ForReadSize_Run();
1050 }
1051 }
1052
1053 if (Config->Event_CallBackFunction_IsSet())
1054 {
1055 Config->Demux_EventWasSent=true;
1056 return;
1057 }
1058 }
1059 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current++;
1060 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size() && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->MI)
1061 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current]->MI->Open_Buffer_Seek(0, 0, (int64u)-1);
1062 }
1063 if (CountOfReferencesToParse)
1064 CountOfReferencesToParse--;
1065 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1066 }
1067 #endif //MEDIAINFO_EVENTS && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1068 ParseReference_Finalize();
1069 if (!Config->File_KeepInfo_Get())
1070 {
1071 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind=Stream_Max;
1072 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos=(size_t)-1;
1073 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->State=10000;
1074 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.empty())
1075 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileSize=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.File_Size;
1076 else if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileSize==(int64u)-1)
1077 {
1078 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileSize=0;
1079 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size(); Pos++)
1080 for (size_t Resource_FileNames_Pos=0; Resource_FileNames_Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames.size(); Resource_FileNames_Pos++)
1081 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileSize+=File::Size_Get(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames[Resource_FileNames_Pos]);
1082 }
1083 delete Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI; Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI=NULL;
1084 }
1085 }
1086}
1087
1088//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1089void File__ReferenceFilesHelper::ParseReference_Finalize ()
1090{
1091 //Removing wrong initial value
1092 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Count_Get(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind)==0 && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos!=(size_t)-1
1093 && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Count_Get(Stream_Video)+Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Count_Get(Stream_Audio)+Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Count_Get(Stream_Image)+Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Count_Get(Stream_Text)+Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Count_Get(Stream_Other))
1094 {
1095 MI->Stream_Erase(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos);
1096 for (sequences::iterator ReferenceTemp=Sequences.begin(); ReferenceTemp!=Sequences.end(); ++ReferenceTemp)
1097 if ((*ReferenceTemp)->StreamKind==Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind && (*ReferenceTemp)->StreamPos!=(size_t)-1 && (*ReferenceTemp)->StreamPos>Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos)
1098 (*ReferenceTemp)->StreamPos--;
1099 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos=(size_t)-1;
1100 }
1101
1102 bool StreamFound=false;
1103 for (size_t StreamKind=Stream_General+1; StreamKind<Stream_Max; StreamKind++)
1104 for (size_t StreamPos=0; StreamPos<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Count_Get((stream_t)StreamKind); StreamPos++)
1105 {
1106 StreamKind_Last=(stream_t)StreamKind;
1107 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos!=(size_t)-1 && StreamKind_Last==Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind && StreamPos==0)
1108 {
1109 StreamPos_To=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos;
1110 StreamFound=true;
1111 }
1112 else
1113 {
1114 size_t ToInsert=(size_t)-1;
1115 for (sequences::iterator ReferencePos=Sequences.begin(); ReferencePos!=Sequences.end(); ++ReferencePos)
1116 if ((*ReferencePos)->StreamKind==StreamKind_Last && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamID<(*ReferencePos)->StreamID)
1117 {
1118 ToInsert=(*ReferencePos)->StreamPos;
1119 break;
1120 }
1121
1122 StreamPos_To=Stream_Prepare((stream_t)StreamKind, ToInsert);
1123 }
1124 StreamPos_From=StreamPos;
1125
1126 ParseReference_Finalize_PerStream();
1127 }
1128
1129 if (!StreamFound && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind!=Stream_Max && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos!=(size_t)-1 && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Info)
1130 {
1131 Ztring MuxingMode=MI->Retrieve(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos, "MuxingMode");
1132 if (!MuxingMode.empty())
1133 MuxingMode.insert(0, __T(" / "));
1134 MI->Fill(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamKind, Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamPos, "MuxingMode", Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Info->Get(Stream_General, 0, General_Format)+MuxingMode, true);
1135 }

1512 MI_Temp->Config.Config_PerPackage->Event_CallBackFunction_Set(Config->Event_CallBackFunction_Get());
1513 }
1514 MI_Temp->Config.File_Names_RootDirectory=FileName(MI->File_Name).Path_Get();
1515 if (!Config->File_TestContinuousFileNames_Get() || Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames.size()>1)
1516 MI_Temp->Option(__T("File_TestContinuousFileNames"), __T("0"));

1518 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->IsMain)
1519 HasMainFile=true;
1520 if (HasMainFile && !Sequences[Sequences_Current]->IsMain)
1521 {
1522 ZtringList ID;
1523 ID.push_back(Ztring::ToZtring((((int64u)MediaInfo_Parser_SideCar)<<56)|Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamID-1));
1524 ID.push_back(Ztring::ToZtring(16));
1525 ID.push_back(Ztring::ToZtring(MediaInfo_Parser_SideCar));
1526 SubFile_IDs.push_back(ID);
1527 }
1528 else if (!Sequences[Sequences_Current]->IsMain)

1530 {
1531 ZtringList ID;
1532 if (MI->StreamIDs_Width[Pos]==0)
1533 ID.push_back(Ztring::ToZtring(-1));
1534 else if (Pos+1==MI->StreamIDs_Size)
1535 ID.push_back(Ztring::ToZtring(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->StreamID));
1536 else
1537 ID.push_back(Ztring::ToZtring(MI->StreamIDs[Pos]));
1538 ID.push_back(Ztring::ToZtring(MI->StreamIDs_Width[Pos]));
1539 ID.push_back(Ztring::ToZtring(MI->ParserIDs[Pos]));
1540 SubFile_IDs.push_back(ID);
1541 }
1542 if (!SubFile_IDs.empty())
1543 {
1544 SubFile_IDs.Separator_Set(0, EOL);
1545 SubFile_IDs.Separator_Set(1, __T(","));
1546 MI_Temp->Option(__T("File_SubFile_IDs_Set"), SubFile_IDs.Read());
1547 }
1548 #endif //MEDIAINFO_EVENTS
1549 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1550 if (Config->Demux_Unpacketize_Get())

1552 if (Config->Demux_Avc_Transcode_Iso14496_15_to_Iso14496_10_Get())

1554 if (Config->Demux_Hevc_Transcode_Iso14496_15_to_AnnexB_Get())
1555 MI_Temp->Option(__T("File_Demux_Hevc_Transcode_Iso14496_15_to_AnnexB"), __T("1"));
1556 if (FrameRate)
1557 MI_Temp->Option(__T("File_Demux_Rate"), Ztring::ToZtring(FrameRate));
1558 else if (!Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.empty() && Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->EditRate) //TODO: per Pos
1559 MI_Temp->Option(__T("File_Demux_Rate"), Ztring::ToZtring(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[0]->EditRate));
1560 switch (Config->Demux_InitData_Get())
1561 {
1562 case 0 : MI_Temp->Option(__T("File_Demux_InitData"), __T("Event")); break;
1563 case 1 : MI_Temp->Option(__T("File_Demux_InitData"), __T("Field")); break;
1564 default: ;
1565 }
1566 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1567 #if MEDIAINFO_IBIUSAGE
1568 if (!Sequences[Sequences_Current]->IbiStream.Infos.empty())
1569 {
1570 ibi Ibi;
1571 Ibi.Streams[(int64u)-1]=new ibi::stream(Sequences[Sequences_Current]->IbiStream);

1600Ztring Duration_Milliseconds2String(int64u DurationM)
1601{
1602 Ztring DurationS;
1603 DurationS+=L'0'+(Char)(DurationM/(10*60*60*1000)); DurationM%=10*60*60*1000;
1604 DurationS+=L'0'+(Char)(DurationM/( 60*60*1000)); DurationM%= 60*60*1000;
1605 DurationS+=L':';
1606 DurationS+=L'0'+(Char)(DurationM/( 10*60*1000)); DurationM%= 10*60*1000;
1607 DurationS+=L'0'+(Char)(DurationM/( 60*1000)); DurationM%= 60*1000;
1608 DurationS+=L':';
1609 DurationS+=L'0'+(Char)(DurationM/( 10*1000)); DurationM%= 10*1000;
1610 DurationS+=L'0'+(Char)(DurationM/( 1000)); DurationM%= 1000;
1611 DurationS+=L'.';
1612 DurationS+=L'0'+(Char)(DurationM/( 100)); DurationM%= 100;
1613 DurationS+=L'0'+(Char)(DurationM/( 10)); DurationM%= 10;
1614 DurationS+=L'0'+(Char)(DurationM);
1615 return DurationS;

1617size_t File__ReferenceFilesHelper::Seek (size_t Method, int64u Value, int64u ID)
1618{
1619 for (Sequences_Current=0; Sequences_Current<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Current++)
1620 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI==NULL && !Sequences[Sequences_Current]->FileNames.empty())
1621 ParseReference_Init();
1622
1623 //Parsing
1624 switch (Method)
1625 {
1626 case 0 :
1627 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1628 {
1629 if (Value)
1630 {
1631 if (Value>MI->Config->File_Size)
1632 return 2; //Invalid value
1633
1634 //Init
1635 if (!Duration)
1636 {
1637 MediaInfo_Internal MI2;
1638 MI2.Option(__T("File_KeepInfo"), __T("1"));
1639 Ztring ParseSpeed_Save=MI2.Option(__T("ParseSpeed_Get"), __T(""));
1640 Ztring Demux_Save=MI2.Option(__T("Demux_Get"), __T(""));
1641 MI2.Option(__T("ParseSpeed"), __T("0"));
1642 MI2.Option(__T("Demux"), Ztring());
1643 size_t MiOpenResult=MI2.Open(MI->File_Name);
1644 MI2.Option(__T("ParseSpeed"), ParseSpeed_Save); //This is a global value, need to reset it. TODO: local value
1645 MI2.Option(__T("Demux"), Demux_Save); //This is a global value, need to reset it. TODO: local value
1646 if (!MiOpenResult)
1647 return (size_t)-1;
1648 Duration=MI2.Get(Stream_General, 0, General_Duration).To_float64()/1000;
1649 }
1650
1651 //Time percentage
1652 float64 DurationF=Duration;
1653 DurationF*=Value;
1654 DurationF/=MI->Config->File_Size;
1655 DurationF*=1000;
1656 int64u DurationM=(int64u)DurationF;
1657
1658 CountOfReferencesToParse=Sequences.size();
1659 bool HasProblem=false;
1660 for (Sequences_Current=0; Sequences_Current<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Current++)
1661 {
1662 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI)
1663 {
1664 Ztring Result;
1665 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size()<=1 || DurationM<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[1]->Demux_Offset_DTS)
1666 {
1667 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current=0;
1668 int64u DurationFTemp=DurationF;
1669 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream!=(int64u)-1)
1670 DurationFTemp+=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream/1000000; // From nanoseconds to milliseconds
1671 Ztring DurationS=Duration_Milliseconds2String((int64u)DurationFTemp);
1672 Result=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Option(__T("File_Seek"), DurationS);
1673 }
1674 else
1675 {
1676 size_t Resources_Current_Temp=1;
1677 while (Resources_Current_Temp<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size() && DurationM>=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->Demux_Offset_DTS)
1678 Resources_Current_Temp++;
1679 Resources_Current_Temp--;
1680 int64u DurationFTemp=DurationF;
1681 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream!=(int64u)-1)
1682 DurationFTemp+=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream/1000000; // From nanoseconds to milliseconds
1683 Ztring DurationS=Duration_Milliseconds2String((int64u)DurationFTemp);
1684 Result=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->MI->Option(__T("File_Seek"), DurationS);
1685 if (Result.empty())
1686 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current=Resources_Current_Temp;
1687 }
1688 if (!Result.empty())
1689 HasProblem=true;
1690 }
1691 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status.reset();
1692 }
1693 Sequences_Current=0;
1694 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
1695 return HasProblem?(size_t)-1:1; //Not supported value if there is a problem (TODO: better info)
1696 }
1697
1698 CountOfReferencesToParse=Sequences.size();
1699 bool HasProblem=false;
1700 for (Sequences_Current=0; Sequences_Current<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Current++)
1701 {
1702 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI)
1703 {
1704 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current=0;
1705 Ztring Result=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Option(__T("File_Seek"), Ztring::ToZtring(Value));
1706 if (!Result.empty())
1707 HasProblem=true;
1708 }
1709 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status.reset();
1710 }
1711 Sequences_Current=0;
1712 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
1713 return HasProblem?(size_t)-1:1; //Not supported value if there is a problem (TODO: better info)
1714 }
1715 #else //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1716 return (size_t)-1; //Not supported
1717 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1718 case 1 :
1719 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1720 {
1721 //Init
1722 if (!Duration)
1723 {
1724 MediaInfo_Internal MI2;
1725 MI2.Option(__T("File_KeepInfo"), __T("1"));
1726 Ztring ParseSpeed_Save=MI2.Option(__T("ParseSpeed_Get"), __T(""));
1727 Ztring Demux_Save=MI2.Option(__T("Demux_Get"), __T(""));
1728 MI2.Option(__T("ParseSpeed"), __T("0"));
1729 MI2.Option(__T("Demux"), Ztring());
1730 size_t MiOpenResult=MI2.Open(MI->File_Name);
1731 MI2.Option(__T("ParseSpeed"), ParseSpeed_Save); //This is a global value, need to reset it. TODO: local value
1732 MI2.Option(__T("Demux"), Demux_Save); //This is a global value, need to reset it. TODO: local value
1733 if (!MiOpenResult)
1734 return (size_t)-1;
1735 Duration=MI2.Get(Stream_General, 0, General_Duration).To_float64()/1000;
1736 }
1737
1738 //Time percentage
1739 float64 DurationF=Duration;
1740 DurationF*=Value;
1741 DurationF/=10; // divided by 10000 for 0.01 percentage then x1000 for milliseconds
1742 int64u DurationM=(int64u)DurationF;
1743
1744 CountOfReferencesToParse=Sequences.size();
1745 bool HasProblem=false;
1746 for (Sequences_Current=0; Sequences_Current<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Current++)
1747 {
1748 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI)
1749 {
1750 Ztring Result;
1751 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size()<2 || Duration<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[1]->Demux_Offset_DTS)
1752 {
1753 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current=0;
1754 int64u DurationFTemp=DurationF;
1755 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream!=(int64u)-1)
1756 DurationFTemp+=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream/1000000; // From nanoseconds to milliseconds
1757 Ztring DurationS=Duration_Milliseconds2String((int64u)DurationFTemp);
1758 Result=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Option(__T("File_Seek"), DurationS);
1759 }
1760 else
1761 {
1762 size_t Resources_Current_Temp=1;
1763 while (Resources_Current_Temp<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size() && Duration>=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->Demux_Offset_DTS)
1764 Resources_Current_Temp++;
1765 Resources_Current_Temp--;
1766 int64u DurationFTemp=DurationF;
1767 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream!=(int64u)-1)
1768 DurationFTemp+=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream/1000000; // From nanoseconds to milliseconds
1769 Ztring DurationS=Duration_Milliseconds2String((int64u)DurationFTemp);
1770 Result=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->MI->Option(__T("File_Seek"), DurationS);
1771 if (Result.empty())
1772 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current=Resources_Current_Temp;
1773 }
1774 if (!Result.empty())
1775 HasProblem=true;
1776 }
1777 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status.reset();
1778 }
1779 Sequences_Current=0;
1780 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
1781 return HasProblem?2:1; //Invalid value if there is a problem (TODO: better info)
1782 }
1783 #else //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1784 return (size_t)-1; //Not supported
1785 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1786 case 2 : //Timestamp
1787 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1788 {
1789 CountOfReferencesToParse=Sequences.size();
1790 for (Sequences_Current=0; Sequences_Current<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Current++)
1791 {
1792 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI)
1793 {
1794 Ztring Result;
1795 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size()<2 || Value<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[1]->Demux_Offset_DTS)
1796 {
1797 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current=0;
1798 int64u ValueTemp=Value;
1799 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream!=(int64u)-1)
1800 ValueTemp+=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream;
1801 Ztring Time; Time.Duration_From_Milliseconds(ValueTemp/1000000);
1802 Result=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Option(__T("File_Seek"), Time);
1803 }
1804 else
1805 {
1806 size_t Resources_Current_Temp=1;
1807 while (Resources_Current_Temp<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size() && Value>=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->Demux_Offset_DTS)
1808 Resources_Current_Temp++;
1809 Resources_Current_Temp--;
1810 int64u ValueTemp=Value;
1811 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream!=(int64u)-1)
1812 ValueTemp+=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->MI->Config.Demux_Offset_DTS_FromStream;
1813 Ztring Time; Time.Duration_From_Milliseconds(ValueTemp/1000000);
1814 Result=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->MI->Option(__T("File_Seek"), Time);
1815 if (Result.empty())
1816 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current=Resources_Current_Temp;
1817 }
1818 if (!Result.empty())
1819 return 2; //Invalid value
1820 }
1821 else
1822 {
1823 //There was a problem, removing Sequence
1824 Sequences.clear();
1825 return Seek(Method, Value, ID);
1826 }
1827 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status.reset();
1828 }
1829 Sequences_Current=0;
1830 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
1831 return 1;
1832 }
1833 #else //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1834 return (size_t)-1; //Not supported
1835 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1836 case 3 : //FrameNumber
1837 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1838 CountOfReferencesToParse=Sequences.size();
1839 for (Sequences_Current=0; Sequences_Current<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Current++)
1840 {
1841 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI)
1842 {
1843 Ztring Result;
1844 if (Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size()<2 || Value<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[1]->Demux_Offset_Frame)
1845 {
1846 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current=0;
1847 Result=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->MI->Option(__T("File_Seek"), __T("Frame=")+Ztring::ToZtring(Value));
1848 }
1849 else
1850 {
1851 size_t Resources_Current_Temp=1;
1852 while (Resources_Current_Temp<Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources.size() && Value>=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->Demux_Offset_Frame)
1853 Resources_Current_Temp++;
1854 Resources_Current_Temp--;
1855 Result=Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->MI->Option(__T("File_Seek"), __T("Frame=")+Ztring::ToZtring(Value-Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources[Resources_Current_Temp]->Demux_Offset_Frame));
1856 if (Result.empty())
1857 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Resources_Current=Resources_Current_Temp;
1858 }
1859 if (!Result.empty())
1860 return 2; //Invalid value
1861 }
1862 Sequences[Sequences_Current]->Status.reset();

1865 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
1866 return 1;
1867 #else //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1868 return (size_t)-1; //Not supported
1869 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1870 default : return 0;

1880size_t File__ReferenceFilesHelper::Stream_Prepare (stream_t StreamKind, size_t StreamPos)
1881{
1882 size_t StreamPos_Last=MI->Stream_Prepare(StreamKind, StreamPos);
1883
1884 for (sequences::iterator ReferencePos=Sequences.begin(); ReferencePos!=Sequences.end(); ++ReferencePos)
1885 if ((*ReferencePos)->StreamKind==StreamKind && (*ReferencePos)->StreamPos>=StreamPos_Last)
1886 if ((*ReferencePos)->StreamPos!=(size_t)-1)

1892//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1893void File__ReferenceFilesHelper::FileSize_Compute ()
1894{
1895 if (MI->Config==NULL)
1896 return;
1897
1898 MI->Config->File_Size=MI->File_Size;
1899
1900 for (size_t Sequences_Pos=0; Sequences_Pos<Sequences.size(); Sequences_Pos++)
1901 {
1902 if (Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->FileSize!=(int64u)-1)
1903 MI->Config->File_Size+=Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->FileSize;
1904 else if (Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->MI && Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->MI->Config.File_Size!=(int64u)-1)
1905 {
1906 MI->Config->File_Size+=Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->MI->Config.File_Size;
1907 #if MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
1908 if (!Config->File_IgnoreSequenceFileSize_Get())
1909 #endif //MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
1910 {
1911 if (!Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->Resources.empty())
1912 for (size_t Pos=1; Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->Resources.size(); Pos++)
1913 for (size_t Resource_FileNames_Pos=0; Resource_FileNames_Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames.size(); Resource_FileNames_Pos++)
1914 MI->Config->File_Size+=File::Size_Get(Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames[Resource_FileNames_Pos]);
1915 }
1916 }
1917 else
1918 {
1919 #if MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
1920 if (!Config->File_IgnoreSequenceFileSize_Get())
1921 #endif //MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
1922 {
1923 if (Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->Resources.empty())
1924 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->FileNames.size(); Pos++)
1925 MI->Config->File_Size+=File::Size_Get(Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->FileNames[Pos]);
1926 else
1927 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->Resources.size(); Pos++)
1928 for (size_t Resource_FileNames_Pos=0; Resource_FileNames_Pos<Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames.size(); Resource_FileNames_Pos++)
1929 MI->Config->File_Size+=File::Size_Get(Sequences[Sequences_Pos]->Resources[Pos]->FileNames[Resource_FileNames_Pos]);
1930 }
1931 }
1932 }

1935//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1936void File__ReferenceFilesHelper::CountOfReferences_ForReadSize_Run ()
1937{
1938 //Computing read buffer size
1939 int64u File_Size_Total=0;
1940 int64u Buffer_Read_Size_Total=MI->Config->File_Buffer_Read_Size_Get();
1941 for (sequences::iterator Reference_Temp=Sequences.begin(); Reference_Temp!=Sequences.end(); ++Reference_Temp)
1942 if ((*Reference_Temp)->MI && (*Reference_Temp)->MI->Config.File_Size!=(int64u)-1)
1943 File_Size_Total+=(*Reference_Temp)->MI->Config.File_Size;
1944 if (File_Size_Total)
1945 for (sequences::iterator Reference_Temp=Sequences.begin(); Reference_Temp!=Sequences.end(); ++Reference_Temp)
1946 if ((*Reference_Temp)->MI)
1947 {
1948 int64u Buffer_Read_Size_Temp=float64_int64s(((float64)(*Reference_Temp)->MI->Config.File_Size)/File_Size_Total*Buffer_Read_Size_Total);
1949 int64u Buffer_Read_Size=1;
1950 while (Buffer_Read_Size<Buffer_Read_Size_Temp)
1951 Buffer_Read_Size<<=1;
1952 (*Reference_Temp)->MI->Config.File_Buffer_Read_Size_Set((size_t)Buffer_Read_Size);
1953 }
1954}
